attributes.magic: ELF 64-bit LSB executable, x86-64, version 1 (SYSV), dynamically linked, interpreter /lib64/ld-linux-x86-64.so.2, for GNU/Linux 2.6.32, not stripped

threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered downloader. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This ELF binary is a downloader and backdoor. It establishes a connection to a hardcoded command and control (C2) server 'reactcdn.windowserrorapis.com' on port 443. After connecting, it sends a beacon and then receives a payload. The payload is XOR-decoded with a single-byte key (0x99) and written to an in-memory file descriptor created via the 'memfd_create' syscall. Finally, it executes the in-memory payload using 'fexecve', masquerading the new process as '[kworker/0:2]' to evade detection.
